SQL Staments: 
DQL:

The commands of SQL that are used to retrieve data from the database are collectively called as DQL. 
So all Select statements comes under DQL.

DDL:

Data Definition Language changes the structure of the table like creating a table, deleting a table, altering a table, etc


Data Manipulation Language;
The commands of SQL that are used to insert data into the database, modify the data of the database and to delete data from the 
database are collectively called as DML.
